Gauteng Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs MEC Lebogang Maile will announce a team of administrators to take over the running of the City of Tshwane. Tshwane has been without mayor and city manager for some time now. TSHWANE - Gauteng Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs MEC Lebogang Maile announced a team of administrators to take over the running of the City of Tshwane. Former Executive Mayor of the West Rand District Mpho Nawa has been announced as the head administrators. Former Johannesburg City Manager Mavela Dlamini has been appointed acting Municipal Manager with immediate effect. They will be supported by 8 other administrators. Tshwane has been without mayor and city manager for some time. The Democratic Alliance is taking the matter to court on Tuesday. Last week, the National Council of Provinces backed the decision to place Tshwane under administration. This after Gauteng Executive Council, led by Premier David Makhura decided to invoke section 139 of the constitution, following the collapse of several council meetings.